                   <a class="tile tile-border-right Default has-hover" data-can-equalizer-watch="grid-outer" href="https://www.rpharms.com/making-a-difference/projects-and-campaigns/mental-health" style="background-image:url(/Portals/0/TileImages/Discussion-in-consultation-room.gif);" target="">
                    <div class="inner-wrap no-pad-left no-pad-right">
                     <div class="inner">
                      <p class="category">
                       Making a difference
                      </p>
                      <h3 class="tile_title h2">
                       Mental Health
                      </h3>
                      <p class="date">
                       <span class="fa fa-calendar-o fa-pad-right">
                       </span>
                       6 June 2018
                      </p>
                      <p class="location">
                       <span class="fa fa-map-marker fa-pad-right">
                       </span>
                       England
                      </p>
                      <div class="hover-content">
                       <p>
                        Many of the medicines used to treat mental health problems are associated with health risks. As the experts in medicines and their use, pharmacists can ensure people get the best outcomes from their medicines, reduce adverse events, minimise avoidable harm and unplanned admissions to hospital, while ensuring resources are used more efficiently to deliver the standard and level of care that people with mental health problems deserve.
                       </p>
                       <p class="read-more-link">
                        Read more
                        <i aria-hidden="true" class="fa fa-angle-right fa-pad-left">
                        </i>
                       </p>
